South African Wheat Declines Following Drop by U.S. Benchmark

-- B y   M k h u l u l i   M a n c o t y w a
-- 
2011-03-02T11:07:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/south-african-wheat-declines-following-drop-by-u-s-benchmark.html
Wheat fell for the first day in
three in  South Africa  after prices dropped in the U.S.  Wheat for May delivery, the most-active contract on the
 South African Futures Exchange , declined 25 rand, or 0.8
percent, to close at 3,165 rand ($455) a metric ton in
Johannesburg.  Wheat for May delivery slid 6.75 cents, or 0.8 percent, to
settle at $8.1025 a bushel on the Chicago Board of Trade
yesterday.  White corn for July delivery fell 17 rand, or 1 percent, to
1,636 rand a ton. Meal made from the grain is South Africaâ€™s
staple food.  Yellow corn for July delivery dropped 12 rand, or 0.7
percent, to 1,690 rand a ton. The grain is used mainly for  animal feed  in South Africa.  The gains or losses for the most active contracts of the
following crops today were as follows. All prices are in rand
